verbose_text: Intracerebral administration of the TLR7 agonist imiquimod leads to pronounced neuroinflammation, with upregulated expression of TNF-alpha, IL-1alpha, IL-1beta, IL-6, and IL-12 as well as the chemokines CCL2, CCL3, CXCL1, CXCL9, and CXCL10.
evidence: expression of TNF-alpha, IL-1alpha, IL-1beta, IL-6, and IL-12 as well as the chemokines
